Males are distinguished from all other members of the ‘ A ’. ogoense group (except for ‘ A ’. caudofasciatum Huber & Radda, 1979 , ‘ A ’. pyrophore, and ‘ A ’.
thysi
) by the presence of narrow dark red bars in the posterior part of the flanks and on the caudal peduncle. Males are distinguished from the latter three species by the above mentioned wide supra-orbital grooves and the unique colour pattern of anterior yellow and posterior purple grey on the flanks.
